nodes.bodyText:
I wonder if we should create a custom lock which is more like what rust is using e.g.
public class RwLock<T> {
  private final ReadWriteLock lock = new ReentrantReadWriteLock();
  private final T value;

  public void withWriteLock(final Consumer<T> action) {
    lock.writeLock().lock();
    try {
      action.accept(value);
    } finally {
      lock.writeLock().unlock();
    }
  }

  public <R> R withReadLock(final Function<T, R> reader) {
    lock.readLock().lock();
    try {
      return reader.apply(value);
    } finally {
      lock.readLock().unlock();
    }
  }
}

Mostly it just feels a bit weird that ProtoArrayForkChoice has locks for ProtoArray rather than ProtoArray itself managing the read/write locks.  Having a class that "locks up" the value and encapsulates the locking makes more sense to me though.  Especially since you then can't ever forget to unlock something.

